# Root README Rules

The root `README.md` is only a lightweight entry point for the SDK. It must stay short, practical, and free of filler.

## Allowed Content

- Project name and one short description of what the SDK does.
- Install command.
- Go version requirement.
- Minimal usage example showing site creation, one resource registration, and handler mounting.
- One sentence that auth and permissions are owned by the host application.
- Command to run the bundled example.
- Links to the hosted documentation and documentation source.

## Prohibited Content

- Do not add long tutorials, API reference tables, route lists, architecture notes, field/widget catalogs, repository implementation details, deployment guides, roadmap text, or marketing copy.
- Do not duplicate content that belongs in the Starlight docs site under `docs/`.
- Do not add badges, banners, screenshots, changelogs, contribution guides, license sections, or unrelated project metadata unless explicitly requested.
- Do not add speculative or aspirational feature descriptions.

## Maintenance Rule

- If the README starts needing more than basic install/use information, move that content into `docs/src/content/docs/` and link to it from the README.
- Keep the README readable in one quick scan.

